The paper focuses on automatic robot design using graph search and evolution, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of graph neural networks for parameterizing control policies suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the algorithm to balance exploration and exploitation suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of computer vision techniques for evaluating the performance of the designed robots suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
